s in japan and overseas sojitz also invests in various sectors and conducts financing activities the broad range of sectors in which sojitz operates includes automobiles energy mineral resources chemicals foodstuff resources agricultural and forestry resources consumer goods and industrial parks sojitz was formed in  by the merger of nissho iwai corporation  nisshō iwai kabushikigaisha and nichimen corporation ニチメン nichimen kabushikigaisha the name sojitz is derived from the names of nissho iwai and nichimen both of which include the character  sun sojitz literally meaning twin suns implies a merger of equals between the two companies the corporate logo is a stylized version of the first character in its japanese name contents  history  nichimen  nissho iwai  merger  current operations  adv films partnership  references  external links historyedit nichimenedit beginning around  the japanese government promoted the development of cotton spinning as an initial means of developing modern industry in japan in the wake of the meiji restoration japans native raw cotton supply proved inadequate to meet demand and there was only one japanese importer of raw cotton at the time making the industry highly reliant on foreign merchants to improve this situation a group of spinning companies established japan cotton trading co ltd 本綿花 nippon menka kabushiki kaisha in osaka in  under the leadership of tsuneki sano a yearold former government official after the russojapanese war nichimen expanded its business from importing the company began cotton spinning operations in manchuria and established offices in china korea germany italy and the united kingdom to supply local markets in  nichimen opened a subsidiary in fort worth texas to enter the raw cotton trade in the united states world war i strained cotton supply in europe boosting nichimens international business further in the late s the company expanded into south america and africa trading in cotton as well as wool food products and machinery the great depression harmed nichimens cotton business spurring the companys diversification beyond cotton to trade in silk rayon and other materials during world war ii nichimen was tapped by the japanese military to manage production of flour matches and starch the company changed its name to nichimen enterprise nichimen jitsugyo in  to reflect its more diverse business the largest zaibatsu trading companies were dismantled after the war giving nichimen an early lead among the sogo shosha in the s and a six percent share of japanese foreign trade by  nichimen became closely affiliated with osakabased sanwa bank in  which financed all of nichimens domestic business nichimen was not the main trading company for the sanwa keiretsu as that position was already held by iwai  co nichimen jitsugyo renamed itself nichimen co ltd in  by  nichimen was trading in steel electronics motor vehicles and fibers in addition to textiles nichimen served as the joint venture partner for nabisco when it began operations in japan in the s nichimen co ltd changed its name to nichimen corporation in  nichimen like other sogo shosha was hit hard by the collapse of the japanese asset price bubble in the early s and subsequently made a strategic shift from the soft businesses of lumber food and chemicals trading to the hard businesses of machinery steel and construction nissho iwaiedit nissho iwai was formed in  by the merger of nissho company and iwai sangyo company nissho company was founded in kobe in  as suzuki  company under the leadership of iwajiro suzuki and naokichi kaneko suzuki was originally a sugar trading firm but later diversified into flour steel tobacco beer insurance shipping and shipbuilding it became the second japanese member of the baltic exchange in london iwai  company was founded as a steel trading firm in  and established a number of prominent group enterprises including daicel nisshin steel tokuyama soda kansai paint and fuji photo film it changed its name to iwai sangyo company in  both nissho and iwai emerged as metals and machinery trading companies after world war ii but were significantly smaller than the four largest sogo shosha competitors mitsubishi corporation mitsui  co itochu and marubeni iwai was poorly managed after the war and was on the brink of failure in the early s while nissho was profitable and successfully expanding overseas the japanese government directed the merger of the two companies in  forming the fifth largest trading company in japan falling back to sixth place in  behind sumitomo corporation sanwa bank played a role in the merger and the combined firm became the trading arm of the sanwa group keiretsu nissho iwai was involved in a corruption scandal in  after it passed on a  million yen bribe from mcdonnell douglas to the director general of the japan defense agency in an attempt to influence the sale of f phantom aircraft to the japan air selfdefense force in the wake of the scandal one nissho iwai executive committed suicide by jumping from the companys headquarters building the scandal was uncovered only three years after a similar scandal involving lockheed and marubeni conspiring to bribe prime minister kakuei tanaka in subsequent years the company had a strong focus on liquefied natural gas and steel trading as well as industrial project development mergeredit nichimen and nissho iwai consolidated on a holding company level in  and consolidated their operating units in  adopting the sojitz name at that time the merged holding company sojitz holdings combined with the merged operating company sojitz corporation in  current operationsedit the current headquarters of sojitz corporation iino building in kasumigaseki chiyoda tokyo today the sojitz group consists of approximately  subsidiaries and affiliates located in japan and throughout the world and it is developing its wideranging general trading company operations in roughly  countries and regions across the globe sojitz through its subsidiary sojitz aerospace company is the largest seller of commercial aircraft in japan as it acts as a sales agent for both boeing and bombardier aerospace it distributes mitsubishi motors and hyundai motors automobiles in various countries and also develops and operates power plants industrial plants in various countries in  it received an order to develop a freight rail corridor between delhi and mumbai in india the sojitz aerospace company also acts as sojitzs primary arm for defense related business sojitz owns oil and natural gas concessions in the north sea gulf of mexico qatar gabon egypt and brazil it owns most of the minerva coal mine in australia and distributes nuclear fuel in japan for areva its operations in the chemicals sector include methanol production in indonesia barite mining in mexico and industrial salt trading in various markets worldwide in november  it signed an agreement with the australian rare earths mining company lynas to import  million worth of rare earth minerals from linass mine in mount weld australia its consumer business operations include trading in grains feed sugar coffee fish wood and paper it owns the japanese rights to several consumer brands such as eastpak and mcgregor adv films partnershipedit in june  sojitz entered into a partnership with american anime distributor adv films this was done as a means of acquiring more titles in the japanese market from this point on virtually all titles that adv acquired were with sojitzs help however in january  adv mysteriously removed a large number of titles from their website all the titles removed were titles acquired since the sojitz collaboration including gurren lagann which had test disks sent out with dubbed episodes as of may  gurren lagann was licensed by bandai entertainment adv films made booth appearances at the anime central  convention but they canceled their planned panel in july  funimation announced the acquisition of thirty of these titles the titles removed from advs website are as follows   centimeters per second ah my goddess flights of fancy both the film and television adaptions of the key visual novel air best student council blade of the phantom master comic party revolution coyote ragtime show devil may cry the  liveaction horror film ghost train guyver the bioboosted armor innocent venus jing king of bandits th heaven jinki extend the  anime remake of yet another key visual novel kanon kurau phantom memory le chevalier deon magikano moeyo ken moonlight mile nerima daikon brothers pani poni dash project blue earth sos pumpkin scissors red garden tokyo majin ufo princess valkyrie the first anime of utawarerumono venus vs virus the wallflower welcome to the nhk and xenosaga referencesedit  a b history sojitz corporation retrieved  april    「」の ブランド・・ロゴマーク辞典 retrieved  april  「」とうは、のとなった「ニチメン（綿實業）」び「商岩井」が、ともに「」をとするであったことにしている。また、「」の「」はおや会とグループとのいパートナーシップをし、「」にはのようなエネルギーにちたグループをするというがめられており、「」というをじて、「おや会とともにし、かしいをしていこう」といういいが現されている。   history of nichimen corporation sojitz corporation retrieved  april    a b c d nichimen corporation history international directory of company histories vol  st james press  retrieved  april    a b history of nissho iwai sojitz corporation retrieved  april    a b nissho iwai kk history international directory of company histories vol  st james press  retrieved  april    suzuki shinichi  the japanese main bank system a transaction cost approach proquest pp –   large stephen s  shōwa japan  taylor  francis p    machinery division pdf sojitz corporation retrieved  june    energy  metal division pdf sojitz corporation retrieved  june    chemicals division pdf sojitz corporation retrieved  june    tabuchi hiroko november   japanese firm in rare earths deal with australian miner the new york times retrieved november     consumer lifestyle business division pdf sojitz corporation retrieved  june    adv teams up with sojitz  news anime news network  retrieved    adv films removes titl